<div id="review_1965488077" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1965488077" />
    <a title="Anna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41878643-anna"><img alt="Anna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1488562610p2/41878643.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1965488077?book_show_action=true">Dec 05, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anna" href="/user/show/41878643-anna">Anna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41878643-anna?shelf=in-english">in-english</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41878643-anna?shelf=st-audio">st-audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41878643-anna?shelf=re-brit">re-brit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41878643-anna?shelf=a-aw-booker">a-aw-booker</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41878643-anna?shelf=2020">2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1965488077" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5053807470541691136">Nicolette McKenzie’s hoarse voice was a perfect match for Claudia, the narrator of the ‘Moon tiger’. She is tough, and self centered, now elderly, and planning to write her very own history of the world. Strangely in the world of Claudia nobody seems to be of any importance, not her husband, not her child and certainly not any of the people that she mentions. Except for her brother perhaps, and also…. except for one more person, in Egypt, during the war….but that was another Claudia, in another </span>
  <span id="freeText5053807470541691136" style="display:none">Nicolette McKenzie’s hoarse voice was a perfect match for Claudia, the narrator of the ‘Moon tiger’. She is tough, and self centered, now elderly, and planning to write her very own history of the world. Strangely in the world of Claudia nobody seems to be of any importance, not her husband, not her child and certainly not any of the people that she mentions. Except for her brother perhaps, and also…. except for one more person, in Egypt, during the war….but that was another Claudia, in another place and in another time.<br />I love the way Claudia’s vulnerability became apparent, how the soft inner centre of her life, the point that divided everything in before and after, came out to the open. And I loved the nostalgia for Egypt that I thought I could hear in Claudia’s words.<br />This is my first Penelope Lively but will certainly not be the last.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="5053807470541691136" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


